    "(2.6)The approximate expressions on the r.h.s. of eqs.",
    "(2.5)-(2.6) hold in the limit V tb → 1, which is an excellent numerical approximation.",
    "The free parameter ε F, that we assume to be real and vary between 0 and 1 in the phenomenological analysis, interpolates between the down-aligned limit for the third generation (ε F → 0, q 3 → q b) and the up-aligned limit (ε F → 1, q 3 → q t), whereq b = V * ub u L + V * cb c L + V * tb t L b L, q t = t L V td d L + V ts s L + V tb b L, (2.7)and the up-and down-type quark fields appearing on the right-hand-side of both equalities are defined in the mass basis.An equivalent way to describe this effect, and to better justify eqs.",
    "(2.5)-(2.6), is to consider the rotation matrices L u,d diagonalizing Y u Y † u and Y d Y † d in the basis where the SMEFT operators are exactly invariant under U(2) q.",
    "We defineL d such that L † d (Y d Y † d)L d = diag(y 2b, y 2 s, y 2 d), and similarly for L u."
